Statements made as to sentencing.  
AS TO COUNT 1 - 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 7 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 63 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4 YEARS.  
Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program. The defendant is not appropriate for the Risk Reduction program.
Court costs and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Complete 300 hours of community service; 
2) No further violations of the law rising to the level of probable cause;
3) Attend and complete a parenting class; 
4) Mental health evaluation and take all prescribed medication; 
5) AODA assessment and comply with any treatment;
6) No use or possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia; 
7) Absolute sobriety with random urine screens (at least once per month); 
8) Attend treatment and counseling programs as determined by agent; 
9) No contact with the victim, victims residence or school, victims family, the City of Glendale, Port Washington Road or any Hotels on Port Washington Road; 
10) Register and comply with the sex offender registry;
11) Obtain/comply with sex offender treatment; 
12) Seek/maintain full time employment;
13) Obtain GED/HSED; 
14) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 
15) Pay all supervision fees;
16) Restitution set at ZERO;
17) Pay applicable costs, surcharges, victim/witness surcharge and assessments; any balance remaining unpaid at that time is to be converted to a civil judgment against the defendant.
If defendant cooperates with authorities regarding the co-actors (specifically the male co-actor) in this matter, the court will allow a motion to modify the sentencing.  
Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting.
